    {
      "content": "Important considerations for SQL Server HADR in Azure",
      "pos": [
        9663,
        9716
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure VMs, storage, and networking have different operational characteristics than an on-premises, non-virtualized IT infrastructure.",
      "pos": [
        9718,
        9851
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A successful implementation of a HADR SQL Server solution in Azure requires that you understand these differences and design your solution to accommodate them.",
      "pos": [
        9852,
        10011
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "High availability nodes in an availability set",
      "pos": [
        10017,
        10063
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Availability sets in Azure enable you to place the high availability nodes into separate Fault Domains (FDs) and Update Domains (UDs).",
      "pos": [
        10065,
        10199
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For Azure VMs to be placed in the same availability set, you must deploy them in the same cloud service.",
      "pos": [
        10200,
        10304
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Only nodes in the same cloud service can participate in the same availability set.",
      "pos": [
        10305,
        10387
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Manage the Availability of Virtual Machines<ept id=\"p1\">](virtual-machines-manage-availability.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        10388,
        10501
